724899f-a.text:
York Avenue, from 69th to 71st Streets, seen from the east side at o9th Street, with clearing on east side in foreground. Excavation for the new New York Hospital and Cornell Medical College buildings is going on on the esst side of the Avenue from 68th to 70th Streets. The buildings on the east side from
700th to 71st Streets are being demolished.
On the west side, the garage on the N.W. corner of 69th Street is new, since 19EO. The other buildings date back to the
1890's and in some cases a little earlier.
Auguat 21, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
The same, not showing the entire N.W. corner of 69th Street.
August 21, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
